Linux Production Server Health Check Automation

Overview

To improve the daily administration of the Stable Manager production server, I developed a reusable Bash health check script that consolidates infrastructure monitoring into a single command.

Instead of manually checking multiple services and logs every day, the script provides a concise overview of the server's health, helping identify infrastructure issues before they impact users.

Objective

Create an automated daily health check capable of monitoring the most important components of a Linux production server:

System uptime and load
Disk utilization
Memory and swap usage
Docker container status
Container restart count
Nginx service
PostgreSQL service
Fail2ban protection
Application errors
HTTP endpoint availability
Overall infrastructure health summary
Technologies
Ubuntu Server
Bash
Docker
Nginx
PostgreSQL
Fail2ban
systemd
journalctl
